    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-04-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="569"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-04-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that the Senate has
                    given its advice and consent to the ratification of the convention signed on the
                    18th instant between the United States and Great Britain for the renewal of the
                    existing <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> in the Behring Sea.</p>
                <p>I shall, at an early date, be glad to effect with you the exchange of
                    ratifications of this convention, should that course be found agreeable to Her
                    Majesty’s Government.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
